= Web UI and Notifications =

== Web Application Role ==
'''Pulse.Web''' is the main user-facing ASP.NET MVC 5 application.

Primary responsibilities:
* render pages and server-side views
* enforce UI-level authorization visibility
* orchestrate authenticated API calls
* host SignalR-based UX interactions where applicable

== Notification UX ==
Pulse has two user notification entry points:

=== Navbar Dropdown ===
* fetches unread, active notifications from API unread endpoint
* optimized for quick awareness and short interaction loops

=== Dedicated Notifications Page ===
* page route renders grouped active notifications
* intended for broader review and triage workflows

=== Mark-As-Read ===
* individual read transactions call API mark-as-read endpoint

== Navigation Surfaces ==
Notifications are reachable from shared navigation components (navbar and sidebar).

== Authorization in UI ==
UI cards/menus/actions should be filtered by module claims to avoid exposing unauthorized navigation paths.

